TITLE: Drawing a Filled Heptagram with SkCanvas in C++
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use SkCanvas to draw a filled heptagram shape. It sets up the canvas, defines points for the star, and uses drawPath to render the shape with a specified paint style.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/skia/blob/main/site/docs/user/api/skcanvas_overview.md#2025-04-08_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    SkPath path;
    const SkScalar R = 115.2f, C = 128.0f;
    path.moveTo(C + R, C);
    for (int i = 1; i < 7; ++i) {
        SkScalar a = 2.6927937f * i;
        path.lineTo(C + R * cos(a), C + R * sin(a));
    }
    path.close();
    SkPaint p;
    p.setAntiAlias(true);
    canvas->drawPath(path, p);
}
```

