TITLE: Handling Coordinate Spaces in SkSL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates coordinate space handling in SkSL. It shows how to adjust coordinates before evaluating an image shader, taking into account that image coordinates use pixel dimensions rather than normalized values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/skia/blob/main/site/docs/user/sksl.md#2025-04-08_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: SkSL
CODE:
```
uniform shader image;
uniform float2 imageSize;

vec4 main(vec2 coord) {
    // Calculate normalized coordinates in [0..1]
    vec2 normalized = coord / imageSize;

    // Flip the y-coordinate
    normalized.y = 1.0 - normalized.y;

    // Convert back to the image's scale
    return image.eval(normalized * imageSize);
}
```

