TITLE: Color Space Management with Uniforms in SkSL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to properly mark uniform variables that contain colors using the layout(color) syntax to ensure proper color space conversion in color-managed workflows.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/skia/blob/main/site/docs/user/sksl.md#2025-04-08_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: SkSL
CODE:
```
// This uniform will be automatically converted to the working color space
layout(color) uniform vec4 color;

// This uniform will be passed through unchanged
uniform vec4 not_a_color;

vec4 main(vec2 coord) {
    float t = coord.x / 256.0;
    // Use different uniforms for top and bottom half
    if (coord.y < 128.0) {
        return mix(vec4(0, 0, 0, 1), not_a_color, t);
    } else {
        return mix(vec4(0, 0, 0, 1), color, t);
    }
}
```

