TITLE: Proof Derivation for Distance Calculation
DESCRIPTION: Mathematical steps showing the derivation of the distance calculation formula for the case when x  0, using geometric properties of similar triangles and the Pythagorean theorem.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/skia/blob/main/site/docs/dev/design/conical/_index.md#2025-04-08_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: latex
CODE:
```
||C_f H|| = ||C_f C_1|| \cdot (||C_f X_P|| / ||C_f P||) = x / \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}
||C_1 H|| = ||C_f C_1|| \cdot (||P X_P|| / ||C_f P||) = y / \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}

||H P_1|| = \sqrt{r_1^2 - ||C_1 H||^2} = \sqrt{r_1^2 - y^2 / (x^2 + y^2)}
```

