TITLE: Corollary 3 Derivation
DESCRIPTION: Algebraic manipulation to derive the simplified formula for the transformation parameter when r_1 > 1, showing the step-by-step process to reach the final result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/skia/blob/main/site/docs/dev/design/conical/_index.md#2025-04-08_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: latex
CODE:
```
x_t &= \frac{x^2 + y^2}{x + \sqrt{(r_1^2 - 1) y^2 + r_1^2 x^2}} \\\\
        &= {
               (x^2 + y^2) \left ( -x + \sqrt{(r_1^2 - 1) y^2 + r_1^2 x^2} \right )
           \over
               \left (x + \sqrt{(r_1^2 - 1) y^2 + r_1^2 x^2} \right )
               \left (-x + \sqrt{(r_1^2 - 1) y^2 + r_1^2 x^2} \right )
           } \\\\
        &= {
               (x^2 + y^2) \left ( -x + \sqrt{(r_1^2 - 1) y^2 + r_1^2 x^2} \right )
           \over
               -x^2 + (r_1^2 - 1) y^2 + r_1^2 x^2
           } \\\\
        &= {
               (x^2 + y^2) \left ( -x + \sqrt{(r_1^2 - 1) y^2 + r_1^2 x^2} \right )
           \over
               (r_1^2 - 1) (x^2 + y^2)
           } \\\\
        &= \left(\sqrt{(r_1^2 - 1) y ^2 + r_1^2 x^2}  - x\right) / (r_1^2 - 1)
```
